    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nHello ðŸ‘‹ \n\nI've been using `lspconfig.util.get_config_by_ft` for a while before having to move to `vim.lsp`. Would it be possible to add it to neovim too? Because of the new way of enabling config `get_config_by_ft` always returns an empty Lua table. As a workaround I'm accessing `vim.lsp.config._configs`, where I can find the info I need, but I guess `._configs` is not a user intended thing that could eventually break?\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAdd `vim.lsp.util.get_config_by_ft` that works as `lspconfig.util.get_config_by_ft` used to.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "```lua\nlocal get_client_by_ft = function(ft)\n\treturn vim.iter(vim.lsp._enabled_configs)\n\t\t:filter(function(name, _)\n\t\t\treturn vim.tbl_contains(vim.lsp.config[name].filetypes, ft)\n\t\tend)\n\t\t:totable()\nend\nvim.print(get_client_by_ft(\"go\"))\n```",
