            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> ```lua\n> local get_client_by_ft = function(ft)\n> \treturn vim.iter(vim.lsp._enabled_configs)\n> \t\t:filter(function(name, _)\n> \t\t\treturn vim.tbl_contains(vim.lsp.config[name].filetypes, ft)\n> \t\tend)\n> \t\t:totable()\n> end\n> vim.print(get_client_by_ft(\"go\"))\n> ```\n\nThis only gets enabled configs. Did the old lspconfig function work like this?\n\nIf you want to get all configs, you need to merge `nvim_get_runtime_file('lsp/*.lua', true)` and `vim.tbl_keys(lsp.config._configs)`, like [how it was done for `:lsp` completion](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/3621af9b970c80d2a6ff36569d7495391599c334/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ex_cmd.lua#L23-L43).",
